:scss
  .embed-container {
    position: relative;
    padding-bottom: 56.25%;
    overflow: hidden;
    max-width: 100%;
    height: 325px;
  }
  .embed-container iframe, .embed-container object, .embed-container embed {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
  }

.row
  .large-8.columns
    = image_tag 'home_banner_1.png'
  .large-4.columns
    .embed-container
      %iframe{src: "https://connect.clickandpledge.com/w/Organization/lacocinasf/paymentwidget/06e3dbaf-d3f9-4dde-96ce-1feec8319d2a", frameborder: "0", allowfullscreen: true}

.row
  .large-12.columns.text-center
    %h1 Be part of defining what La Cocina can mean
    .row
      %p The mission of La Cocina is to cultivate low-income food entrepreneurs as they formalize and grow their businesses by providing affordable commercial kitchen space, industry-specific technical assistance and access to market opportunities. We focus primarily on women from communities of color and immigrant communities. Our vision is that entrepreneurs will become economically self-sufficient and contribute to a vibrant economy doing what they love to do.

    .row.text-center.col-5
      %h2.copper Our Participants
      .large-2.columns
        %div.icon-box
          = image_tag 'icons/chef.svg'
        %p.subheading.secondary Have a strong desire to own a business
      .large-2.columns
        %div.icon-box
          = image_tag 'icons/food.svg'
        %p.subheading.secondary Have a high quality food product often sold informally
      .large-2.columns
        %div.icon-box
          = image_tag 'icons/apron.svg'
        %p.subheading.secondary Have 6 employees or less
      .large-2.columns
        %div.icon-box
          = image_tag 'icons/savings.svg'
        %p.subheading.secondary Have $35,000 worth of assets or less
        %p.subtext (taking liabilities into account)
      .large-2.columns.end
        %div.icon-box
          = image_tag 'icons/income.svg'
        %p.subheading.secondary Are low to very low income
        %p.subtext (according to U.S. Department of Housing and Urban Development guidelines)
    .row.text-center
      .large-4.columns
        %h4.copper The Need
        %p The idea for La Cocina emerged the recognition of strong desire among immigrant women in the Mission to start their own food businesses and the realization of the obstacles preventing them from doing so.
      .large-4.columns
        %h4.copper What They Have
        %p Entrepreneurial Spirit, Business Plans and <strong>Phenomenal Food</strong>.
      .large-4.columns
        %h4.copper What They Lack
        %p Access to markets, Commercial Kitchen space, Technical Assistance and Access to Capital.
    .row.text-center
      %h2.copper Our Entrepreneurs
      = render partial: 'partials/businesses'
    %hr
    .row.text-center
      %h2.copper Local Community
      .large-8.large-offset-2.columns.end
        %p.subheading.secondary
          We also aim to provide resources to local entrepreneurs who are not part of our program, as well as delicious products to food enthusiasts throughout the Bay Area.
    .row.text-center.vertically-centered
      .large-4.columns.right-border
        %h3 $2.9 million
        %p.subtext in revenue
        %h3 jobs
        %p.subtext full time, part time and contractors
      .large-4.columns
        %h3 $435,000 owners pay
        %p.subtext 37% increase from 2013
        %h3 $850,000
        %p.subtext wages paid
      .large-4.columns.text-left
        %p The milestones that La Cocina and its client businesses reached this year continue to affirm our belief that, given the right resources, any business can succeed. That is why we are presenting you with an opportunity to support La Cocina and help these business achieve that success.

        %p Every dollar counts. For every $1 you donate, the businesses generate $3 of revenue for the local economy plus an average of 2 jobs per business. Imagine what your donation of $50, $75, or $100 will mean to aspiring entrepreneurs, their families, and our community.
    %hr
    .row.text-center
      %h2.copper What Your Donation Helps to Support
      %p <strong>100% of your donation goes to program operating costs which allow La Cocina to provide low income entrepreneurs with the following resources:</strong>
      .large-4.columns
        %p.subheading.secondary Subsidized commercial kitchen space
        %ul.text-left
          %li Program Participants pay an average of $13/hour for kitchen rental space.
          %li Commercial users pay an average of $35/hour for kitchen rental space
      .large-4.columns
        %p.subheading.secondary Workshops
        %ul.text-left
          %li La Cocina offers workshops to its clients and the general public in various aspects of food business knowledge.
      .large-4.columns
        %p.subheading.secondary Industry-Specific Technical Assistance
        %ul.text-left
          %li A rich network more than 100 dedicated professionals provides free or subsidized technical assistance in marketing, operations, product, sales and finances for food businesses.  
    .row.text-center
      .large-4.large-offset-4.columns.end
        %p.subheading.secondary Access to Markets and Market Positioning
        %ul.text-left
          %li La Cocina connects vendors to market opportunities and co-branding  for the mainstream market.
    .row.text-center
      = link_to 'Donate Now', 'https://co.clickandpledge.com/sp/d2/default.aspx?wid=119632', class: 'button wide'
